es.', 'Synergism', 'Viloxazine', NULL, 'Major', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/131814/', '[1] Bijl D "The serotonin syndrome." Neth J Med 62 (2004): 309-13[2] Mills KC "Serotonin syndrome: A clinical update." Crit Care Clin 13 (1997): 763[3] Ciraulo DA, Shader RI "Fluoxetine drug-drug interactions. II." J Clin Psychopharmacol 10 (1990): 213-7[4] Martin TG "Serotonin syndrome." Ann Emerg Med 28 (1996): 520-6[5] Noveske FG, Hahn KR, Flynn RJ "Possible toxicity of combined fluoxetine and lithium." Am J Psychiatry 146 (1989): 1515[6] Sternbach H "The serotonin syndrome." Am J Psychiatry 148 (1991): 705-13[7] "Product Information. Pristiq (desvenlafaxine)." Wyeth Laboratories, Philadelphia, PA.[8] "Product Information. Effexor (venlafaxine)." Wyeth-Ayerst Laboratories, Philadelphia, PA.[9] "Product Information. Cymbalta (duloxetine)." Lilly, Eli and Company, Indianapolis, IN.[10] "Product Information. Viibryd (vilazodone)." Trovis Pharmaceuticals LLC, New Haven, CT.[11] Chan BSH, Graudins A, Whyte IM, Dawson AH, Braitberg G, Duggin GG "Serotonin syndrome resulting from drug interactions." Med J Aust 169 (1998): 523-5[12] Muly EC, McDonald W, Steffens D, Book S "Serotonin syndrome produced by a combination of fluoxetine and lithium." Am J Psychiatry 150 (1993): 1565[13] Hadley A, Cason MP "Mania resulting from lithium-fluoxetine combination." Am J Psychiatry 146 (1989): 1637-8[14] "Product Information. Meridia (sibutramine)." Knoll Pharmaceutical Company, Whippany, NJ.[15] "Product Information. Fetzima (levomilnacipran)." Forest Pharmaceuticals, St. Louis, MO.[16] Sobanski T, Bagli M, Laux G, Rao ML "Serotonin syndrome after lithium add-on medication to paroxetine." Pharmacopsychiatry 30 (1997): 106-7[17] "Product Information. Savella (milnacipran)." Forest Pharmaceuticals, St. Louis, MO.[18] Warrington SJ, Ankier SI, Turner P "Evaluation of possible interactions between ethanol and trazodone or amitriptyline." Neurop